I play both a Druid and a Cleric. It really pisses me off when people try to tell me how to play those (or any) classes. The other day i had a perfect example:<BR>My Druid (level 30) was hunting in Frontier Mountains. My group had a Cleric and a Bard. I also had Clarity. I was at 80% mana (after snaring and dotting the pull) so I started taking swings at the pull. Cleric also had full (or nearly full) mana. One of the group members started yelling at me for meleeing. I tried to explain to they guy that if I couldnt handle healing the group (keep in mind that i was the backup healer after a cleric with full mana) then we were screwed anyway. Wouldnt listen to me, just kept telling me that I shouldnt melee. In cases like that i just leave the group.<BR>I could understand yelling at healers for meleeing if it could endanger the group, but I obviously wasnt.<P>--------------------<P>"Oh no, not again"<BR>            -a bowl of petunias
