This is what most meleeing casters think.  First, they want to maybe make a hybrid, to melee AND cast spells.  Then they see that they get their spells at a later time in their life when the pure caster gets them first AND more spells, so they just make a caster and melee with it.  I was grouped with a level 24 wizard who just didnt want to stop meleeing just today.<P>Ok, lets put it this way...<P>Wizard, Cleric, Warrior, Rogue, Druid and Enchanter are all grouped..  Ok, now the warrior is healer with bandages; The wizard melees and is backup healer with bandages; The cleric practices fletching; the rogue nukes with his throwing daggers, the druid practices divination and the enchanter tanks.  Good group?  Oh well, at least we're all having fun, til of course, WE DIE, then the game turns frustrating.<P>Choose a class that is efficient with your playing style and learn to live with it, cause the sooner, the better.
