<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by FoxDragoon:<BR><STRONG><BR>The set-up that I provided (warrior bandaging, chanter tanking, etc..) was an exagerated view of an ineffective group.  If your caster is meleeing hes not helping the group in his full potential.  People like people who play classes like they are supposed to, thats free advice on my part.  The grouped picked you (lets say druid) to be backup healer and nuker, not to melee.  things you get away doing in the early levels will get you killed in the late game.<P>Go ahead and melee, I have no problem with it, unless you are grouped with me     <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Oh, I know you were exaggerating... I'm quite fond of hyperbole myself <g>.<P>As far as people liking people "who play classes like they are supposed to"... well, I'd prefer grouping with people who can hold their own and provide some fun at the same time, even if it means losing a bit of efficiency.  But that's just personal preference.<P>As far as playing how I want, unless I'm grouped with you... it sounds like you enjoy pushing the edge, and going to places which require top efficiency constantly.  If I go someplace like that, I'm buffing, healing, and <I>maybe</I> tossing a Root or Stun if the situation warrants.  Nukes are <I>extemely</I> rare, but if the "real" nukers are OOM, I've got a mana reserve, and we need to kill something NOW, I'll toss in a nuke.  In groups like this, I would probably never be in a position (due to mana) where I would melee, except maybe for the first 30-45 seconds of the first fight.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>But, honestly, I generally prefer less intense battles in EQ.  EQ is my chance to wind down and relax, and constant hard-fought battles tend to be counterproductive to why I'm playing.  So, at the camps I'm usually at, a little controlled silliness, planned inefficiency, is not a risk and does not put anyone at risk.<P>Which way is "right"?  Neither, of course.  Every situation is different, and I don't think people should try to force their ways onto others.<P>Make suggestions?  Of course.<BR>Ask that someone stop clowning around at difficult spots?  Sure.<BR>Go off on someone because they don't go for maximum efficiency at an extremely safe spot?  Bah, I'd tell them to disband me if I wasn't already Gating out.
