<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Why SHOULD healers be allowed to melee, at least at lower levels?<P>Imho the reason is quite simple. Outside breaking the boredom of the heal/buff/med/ask-for-clarity routine, going melee and taking a few hits if possible is the only way to improve your defense skill and keep it as high as possible. Which is nearly impossible at higher levels.<BR>I guess you all know the taunt effect healing and how deadly it can be for the healers when the "i'll-teach-ya-how-ta-play-lil-healer" tank makes a bad pull and brings a good train to the group    <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"> . It means a good cleric must have high ac... and defense sure helps a lot.<P>And speaking of efficiency...  <IMG SRC="rolleyes.gif" border="0">  Hey people, remember it is just a game! Enjoy at little! Have fun! And keep this efficiency thingy for work.   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"> It was a lvl 30 that made the post, we are not talking about lvl 55+ raids.<P>Btw, why should only melee purpose classes have the all fun? Do not forget healers are  keeping you alive, so you should better be kind to them!   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>My 2 cp...     <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Moryagorn
