If you want to raise your defense do what I did, do it by yourself.  Ok, this only applies to priest classes (int casters are going to get hit for max dmg practically all of the time no matter what their ac is).  Pull a blue to the zone line, melee it, heal yourself til oom, med, repeat.  Got my defense all the way to 200 with my cleric this way, all by myself, this was at late level 40's, too.  Offense: just ask a group if you can hit the mob to raise it.<P>I can certainly relate to the "start a melee if you dont like casting" subject.  I played a cleric to 51 and I said "Am I just going to med/heal  51-60?"  I decided I wasn't, so I started a rogue, learned the class and loved it.  Best decision I've ever done in this game.  (and notice how rogues dont have the option to cast spells, hint* hint* we're meleers, not caster  <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"> ) <P>I love this game, I have fun and I love all the social aspect this game provides.  I'm not a perfectionist (oh God no).  What I've been trying to say all along is that you might be like me, and find that a rogue might be more of your character than a caster and enjoy the game more this way.<P>"Btw, why should only melee purpose classes have the all fun?"<BR>Think about what you just said   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
